org.pircbotx.hooks.events

Class IncomingFileTransferEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pircbotx.hooks.Event
      • org.pircbotx.hooks.events.IncomingFileTransferEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Event>, GenericDCCEvent, GenericEvent, GenericUserEvent

    public class IncomingFileTransferEvent
extends Event
implements GenericDCCEvent
    This event is dispatched whenever a DCC SEND request is sent to the PircBotX. This means that a client has requested to send a file to us. By default there are no listeners for this event, which means that all DCC SEND requests will be ignored by default. If you wish to receive the file, then you must listen for this event and call the receive method on the DccFileTransfer object, which connects to the sender and downloads the file.

    Example: 

     DccFileTransfer transfer = event.getTransfer();
 // Use the suggested file name.
 File file = transfer.getFile();
 // Receive the transfer and save it to the file, allowing resuming.
 transfer.receive(file, true);

    Warning: Receiving an incoming file transfer will cause a file to be written to disk. Please ensure that you make adequate security checks so that this file does not overwrite anything important!

    If you allow resuming and the file already partly exists, it will be appended to instead of overwritten. If resuming is not enabled, the file will be overwritten if it already exists.

    Author:
    Leon Blakey
